$OpenBSD$

Replace g_file_set_contents() with g_file_set_contents_full() to set
explicit file permissions (0640) and use atomic write via
G_FILE_SET_CONTENTS_CONSISTENT (write to temp file, then rename(2)).

The g_file_test() existence check is preserved to prevent silently
overwriting an existing palette file.  The atomic rename(2) used by
CONSISTENT mode avoids partially-written files if the process is
interrupted, and replaces any symlink at the destination path with a
real file rather than following it.

Note: on OpenBSD, the unveil(2) call in patch-src_main_c-openbsd-pledge-unveil
restricts filesystem access to only the unveiled paths, providing additional
mitigation against any residual TOCTOU window between the g_file_test check
and the write.  Line numbers account for the +4 lines from patch-src_main_c
and +15 lines from patch-src_main_c-openbsd-pledge-unveil.

Index: src/main.c
--- src/main.c.orig
+++ src/main.c
@@ -175,7 +175,9 @@
           exit (EXIT_FAILURE);
         }
 
-      if (!g_file_set_contents (dest, contents, len, &error))
+      if (!g_file_set_contents_full (dest, contents, len,
+                                     G_FILE_SET_CONTENTS_CONSISTENT,
+                                     0640, &error))
         {
           g_printerr ("%s: %s\n", _("Error"), error->message);
           exit (EXIT_FAILURE);
 